{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01H8ok4kJRjpSCZh4bgnTWbG","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# mongodb/custom-roles\n2\t# MongoDB custom-roles task\n3\t\n4\tparams:\n5\t  cluster_prefix:\n6\t    default: mongodb-replica\n7\t    description: StatefulSet name of the replica set members.\n8\t  replica_set_name:\n9\t    default: mongodb-replica\n10\t    description: MongoDB replica set _id used when initiating the set.\n11\t  admin_secret_name:\n12\t    default: admin-user-password\n13\t    description: Kubernetes Secret holding the admin user's password.\n14\t  reporting_secret_name:\n15\t    default: reporting-user-password\n16\t    description: Kubernetes Secret holding the reporting user's password.\n17\t  admin_username:\n18\t    default: admin-user\n19\t    description: Username of the MongoDB admin user.\n20\t  reporting_username:\n21\t    default: reporting-user\n22\t    description: Username of the reporting user.\n23\t  app_database:\n24\t    default: appdb\n25\t    description: Application database holding the reporting collections.\n26\t  reports_collection:\n27\t    default: reports\n28\t    description: Collection backing the reporting dashboards.\n29\t  raw_collection:\n30\t    default: raw\n31\t    description: Collection with ingestion data that must not be exposed.\n32\t  bad_role_name:\n33\t    default: rawRead\n34\t    description: Overly-permissive role initially granted to the reporting user.\n35\t\n36\tprompt: |\n37\t  A 3-member MongoDB replica set is running in the mongodb namespace.\n38\t  Authentication is enabled. Passwords are stored in these Secrets:\n39\t  - {{params.admin_secret_name}}\n40\t  - {{params.reporting_secret_name}}\n41\t\n42\t  Reporting dashboards are failing for {{params.reporting_username}} after a permissions change.\n43\t  Dashboards are built from {{params.app_database}}.{{params.reports_collection}}. {{params.app_database}}.{{params.raw_collection}} contains ingestion data and\n44\t  must not be exposed. Restore the minimum access needed for reporting dashboards.\n45\t\n46\t  Notes:\n47\t  - Do not use operators or CRDs.\n48\t\n49\tnamespace_contract:\n50\t  required_roles: []\n51\t\n52\tmetrics:\n53\t  - time_to_first_mutation\n54\t\n55\tpreconditionUnits:\n56\t  - name: mongo_env_ready\n57\t    on_probe_fail: skip\n58\t    probe:\n59\t      # AUTHORITATIVE skip-if-running probe (P32): succeed when the canonical\n60\t      # StatefulSet exists OR any pod is Running, so the destructive namespace\n61\t      # rebuild below is skipped on an inherited cluster even if its pods are\n62\t      # momentarily not Running (mid-restart from a prior stage) -- the\n63\t      # StatefulSet persists across that window. The bare `grep -c Running`\n64\t      # could miss such a cluster and clobber inherited state.\n65\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get statefulset {{params.cluster_prefix}} >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n mongodb get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -q Running'\"\n66\t        timeout_sec: 10\n67\t    apply:\n68\t      - command: |\n69\t          /bin/sh -c '\n70\t          kubectl delete namespace mongodb --ignore-not-found=true; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/mongodb --timeout=120s || true\n71\t          '\n72\t        sleep: 2\n73\t      - command: \"kubectl create namespace mongodb\"\n74\t        sleep: 1\n75\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/custom-roles/resource/secrets.yaml\"\n76\t        sleep: 1\n77\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/custom-roles/resource/services.yaml\"\n78\t        sleep: 1\n79\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/custom-roles/resource/statefulset.yaml\"\n80\t        sleep: 5\n81\t      - command: |\n82\t          for i in $(seq 1 120); do\n83\t            ready=$(kubectl -n mongodb get sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} -o jsonpath='{.status.readyReplicas}' 2>/dev/null)\n84\t            if [ \"${ready:-0}\" -ge 3 ]; then\n85\t              exit 0\n86\t            fi\n87\t            sleep 5\n88\t          done\n89\t          exit 1\n90\t        sleep: 2\n91\t      # Pod-Ready != mongod accepting TCP (§1.10): ping-until-ok before rs.initiate.\n92\t      - command: |\n93\t          for i in $(seq 1 30); do\n94\t            kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval 'db.runCommand({ping:1}).ok' 2>/dev/null | grep -q 1 && exit 0\n95\t            sleep 3\n96\t          done\n97\t          exit 1\n98\t        sleep: 2\n99\t      - command: |\n100\t          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\n101\t          rs.initiate({_id:\"{{params.replica_set_name}}\",members:[\n102\t            {_id:0,host:\"mongodb-replica-0.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},\n103\t            {_id:1,host:\"mongodb-replica-1.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},\n104\t            {_id:2,host:\"mongodb-replica-2.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"}\n105\t          ]})'\n106\t        sleep: 5\n107\t      - command: |\n108\t          for i in $(seq 1 20); do\n109\t            kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval 'db.hello().isWritablePrimary' | grep true && exit 0\n110\t            sleep 3\n111\t          done\n112\t          exit 1\n113\t        sleep: 2\n114\t      - command: |\n115\t          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\n116\t          db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n117\t            user: \"{{params.admin_username}}\",\n118\t            pwd: \"admin123password\",\n119\t            roles: [\n120\t              {role: \"clusterAdmin\", db: \"admin\"},\n121\t              {role: \"userAdminAnyDatabase\", db: \"admin\"},\n122\t              {role: \"readWriteAnyDatabase\", db: \"admin\"}\n123\t            ]\n124\t          })'\n125\t        sleep: 2\n126\t      - command: |\n127\t          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \\\n128\t          \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:admin123password@localhost:27017/admin\" \\\n129\t          --eval 'db.getSiblingDB(\"{{params.app_database}}\").createRole({\n130\t            role: \"{{params.bad_role_name}}\",\n131\t            privileges: [\n132\t              { resource: { db: \"{{params.app_database}}\", collection: \"{{params.raw_collection}}\" }, actions: [\"find\"] }\n133\t            ],\n134\t            roles: []\n135\t          })'\n136\t        sleep: 2\n137\t      - command: |\n138\t          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \\\n139\t          \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:admin123password@localhost:27017/admin\" \\\n140\t          --eval 'db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n141\t            user: \"{{params.reporting_username}}\",\n142\t            pwd: \"reporting123password\",\n143\t            roles: [{role: \"{{params.bad_role_name}}\", db: \"{{params.app_database}}\"}]\n144\t          })'\n145\t        sleep: 2\n146\t      - command: |\n147\t          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \\\n148\t          \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:admin123password@localhost:27017/admin\" \\\n149\t          --eval 'db.getSiblingDB(\"{{params.app_database}}\").{{params.reports_collection}}.insertMany([{x:1},{x:2},{x:3}], {writeConcern:{w:1}})'\n150\t        sleep: 2\n151\t      - command: |\n152\t          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \\\n153\t          \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:admin123password@localhost:27017/admin\" \\\n154\t          --eval 'db.getSiblingDB(\"{{params.app_database}}\").{{params.raw_collection}}.insertMany([{x:10},{x:11}], {writeConcern:{w:1}})'\n155\t        sleep: 2\n156\t    verify:\n157\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n158\t        timeout_sec: 10\n159\t\n160\t  - name: admin_user_fixture\n161\t    # Composition self-sufficiency